### Context Islands — Detailed Design

#### Detection Heuristics

| Island Type | Detection Signal |
|---|---|
| **Natural Language** | High alpha ratio, sentence boundaries, common word frequency |
| **Source Code** | Keywords (`if`, `for`, `def`, `class`, etc.), brace density, indentation regularity |
| **JSON** | `{`, `"key":`, balanced brackets, UTF-8 only |
| **XML/HTML** | `<tag>`, balanced tags, attribute patterns |
| **CSV** | Regular delimiter count per line, quoted fields |
| **Markdown** | `#` headers, `*`/`_` emphasis, `` ` `` code fences |
| **Log** | Timestamp prefix, level labels, repeated template prefix |
| **Binary** | High non-printable ratio — falls back to a general binary mode |

#### Predictor Assignment Per Island

| Island | Active Predictors |
|---|---|
| Natural Language | Word model, phrase model, char model |
| Source Code | Grammar model, structural model, char model |
| JSON | Structural model, key model, value model |
| XML | Tag model, attribute model, text model |
| CSV | Record model, field model |
| Log | Template model, timestamp model |
| Markdown | Structure model, word model |

### Three-Tier Dictionary System

```
Tier 1: Global Dictionary
  ├─ Built from entire corpus (pre-trained or corpus-scan)
  ├─ Contains universal high-frequency phrases: "function", "return", "the", etc.
  └─ Size: ~64KB–256KB

Tier 2: Document Dictionary
  ├─ Built per input file
  ├─ Contains document-specific frequent patterns
  └─ Size: ~8KB–64KB

Tier 3: Block Dictionary
  ├─ Built per 64KB–256KB block
  ├─ Hyper-local frequent phrases
  └─ Size: ~1KB–8KB
```

Encoder selects the **cheapest representation** for each token across all three tiers.

### Parallel CPU–GPU Pipeline (Concurrency Model)

```
Time →
CPU:  [Analyze Block N+1] [Optimize Dict/Grammar N] [Mix Probabilities N-1] [Archive N-2]
GPU:  [Preprocess Block N] [Pattern Mine N]          [rANS Encode N-1]
```

- Uses CUDA Streams and CPU thread pools to maintain full overlap.
- CPU and GPU are never both idle at the same time.

