## 7. Goals & Success Criteria

### Primary Goals

| Goal | Target Metric |
|---|---|
| Compression ratio on text corpora | Within 5–10% of CMIX on Canterbury/Silesia text files |
| Compression speed | ≥ 10× faster than CMIX at similar ratio settings |
| Decompression speed | ≥ 100 MB/s (at minimum), targeting 500 MB/s+ |
| Memory usage | ≤ 4 GB RAM (vs CMIX's 32 GB+) |
| GPU utilization | ≥ 70% sustained during GPU phases |
| CPU utilization | ≥ 80% average across all cores during CPU phases |

### Secondary Goals

| Goal | Target |
|---|---|
| Beat XZ -9 on pure text compression ratio | Yes |
| Approach Brotli quality=11 ratio on web content | Yes |
| Beat Zstd -22 (ultra) on source code corpora | Yes |
| Lossless round-trip verified via BLAKE3 | 100% required |
| `.htx` format: random-access decompression | Phase 13 |
| Streaming compression | Phase 13 |

### Non-Goals (Out of Scope)

- Binary file compression (images, video, executables) — text-only
- Lossy compression of any kind
- Real-time streaming in Phase 1–7

