| **Wikipedia dump** | Large natural language corpus | Natural language prediction quality |
| **JSON datasets** | Synthetic + real API responses | JSON Context Island validation |
| **Log datasets** | Apache/nginx/syslog | Log Context Island validation |

### Competitor Baselines

| Compressor | Mode Tested | Why |
|---|---|---|
| **Zstd** | -3 (default), -19, --ultra -22 | Modern fast compressor |
| **Brotli** | q=6, q=11 | Web standard |
| **XZ** | -6, -9 | High-ratio archiver |
| **7-Zip** | -mx=5, -mx=9 | Common archiver |
| **PAQ8pxd** | default | Near-CMIX performance |
| **CMIX** | default | Gold standard ratio |

### Metrics Captured

For each (corpus file, compressor, mode) triple:

- Compressed size (bytes)
- Compression ratio (= original / compressed)
- Compression time (wall clock, ms)
- Decompression time (wall clock, ms)
- Peak RSS memory (MB)
- Throughput (MB/s) both directions
- Bits per byte (bpb = compressed_bits / original_bytes)

### Benchmark Tooling

- **Google Benchmark** — micro-benchmarks for individual pipeline stages
- **Tracy Profiler** — frame-based profiler, good for pipelined workloads
- **Nsight Compute** — per-kernel GPU roofline analysis
- **Nsight Systems** — system-wide CPU+GPU timeline
- **Intel VTune** — CPU cache and instruction analysis
- **perf** — Linux-native profiling (or WPA on Windows)

