## Appendix A: Terminology Glossary

| Term | Definition |
|---|---|
| **bpb** | Bits per byte — primary compression quality metric. Lower is better. |
| **Context Island** | A contiguous region of text with a uniform semantic type (NL, code, JSON, etc.) |
| **rANS** | Range ANS — arithmetic ANS variant; preferred for GPU due to parallelizability |
| **tANS** | Tabled ANS — lookup-table ANS variant; fastest on CPU |
| **SLP** | Straight-Line Program — the formal model underlying grammar compression |
| **SSE** | Secondary Symbol Estimation — probability refinement layer in CMIX/PAQ |
| **Re-Pair** | Recursive Pairing — offline grammar compression algorithm used in HyperCore |
| **bpb target** | HyperCore v1.0 aspirational target: < 1.8 bpb on enwik8 |
| **Context Mixing** | Combining multiple model predictions via weighted averaging |
| **.htx** | HyperCore's proprietary lossless archive format |

